# git-push-verify — from Cursor

Canonical definition: `.claude/commands/git-push-verify.md`

**To run from Claude Code terminal:** type `/git-push-verify`

**To run manually from Cursor's terminal panel:**

### Stage
```bash
git add -A
```

### Commit (paste this whole block — matches `/git-push-verify` Step 4)

```bash
git commit -m "$(cat <<'COMMITMSG'
feat: project harness v1.0 — enforcement system, docs, and video explainer

Harness infrastructure:
- AGENTS.md charter, CLAUDE.md mandatory reads, .ai/protocols/ (2 protocols)
- .cursor/rules/: 3 auto-loaded pointer rule files
- .claude/hooks/: 4 enforcement scripts (session block, write gate, docs gate)

Documentation: docs-surface-classifier, documentation-update-flow,
.ai/docs/ baseline package, docs/ product package

Tooling: /github-setup (HTTPS+PAT or SSH), /git-push-verify (stage, commit, push, verify)

Product: harness-video/ (Remotion 8-scene explainer, ~120s, 1280x720)
    Scenes 00–07: rules, hooks, docs tree, React example, todo lifecycle, dual-tool flow, file map
COMMITMSG
)"
```

### Push — choose transport (read `push_transport` from `.ai/config/project.json`)

**SSH** (`"push_transport": "ssh"` — uses local keys; host-key prompt on first connect):

```bash
REPO_URL=$(python3 -c "import json; d=json.load(open('.ai/config/project.json')); print(d['github']['repo_url'])")
REPO_PATH="${REPO_URL#https://github.com/}"
git remote set-url origin "git@github.com:${REPO_PATH}.git"
BRANCH=$(git branch --show-current)
git push --set-upstream origin "$BRANCH"
```

**HTTPS** (default / `"push_transport": "https"` — PAT required at runtime, never stored):

```bash
REPO_URL=$(python3 -c "import json; d=json.load(open('.ai/config/project.json')); print(d['github']['repo_url'])")
USERNAME=$(python3 -c "import json; d=json.load(open('.ai/config/project.json')); print(d['github']['username'])")
read -s -p "GitHub PAT: " PAT
REPO_PATH="${REPO_URL#https://github.com/}"
BRANCH=$(git branch --show-current)
git push "https://${USERNAME}:${PAT}@github.com/${REPO_PATH}.git" --set-upstream origin "$BRANCH"
unset PAT
```

### Fetch and verify
```bash
git fetch origin
BRANCH=$(git branch --show-current)
git log "origin/${BRANCH}" --oneline --graph -8
git remote -v
gh repo view 2>/dev/null || python3 -c "import json; print(json.load(open('.ai/config/project.json'))['github']['repo_url'])"
```

Security: PAT (HTTPS only) is read into a shell variable, used once, then immediately unset. Never written to disk. SSH uses your OS keychain / agent only.
